{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b009f181-e539-41a3-a68a-1a5d1b5b45aa","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the **`webapi`** template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n### Authentication options (`--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD (organizational) |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n### Example with auth:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain myorg.onmicrosoft.com\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` if you need custom token validation. Want me to scaffold a project with a specific auth setup?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9dccb9db-b593-4b37-8a95-790e7733386a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":269,"requestId":"C7C6:3B680:6DAC977:75EE3F4:6A03CBBA"},"id":"194b5efe-8de4-4561-807f-587f551ab95b","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:25.481Z","parentId":"bfc66f09-67ae-4c4d-af21-a2ae5d5b6c84"}
